The paper deals with image stitching, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed warps are based on optimization techniques, which are also commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the proposed method involves comparing it to state-of-the-art methods, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG).
